cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper is about model-based reinforcement learning using generative models. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on learning and querying generative models. The second likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses the use of learned environment models for decision making. The third likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the experiments involve Atari games from the Arcade Learning Environment and the models learn from raw pixels. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics) as the paper discusses the potential of using learned environment models for planning. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control) as the paper deals with predicting outcomes of sequences of actions.
